The product idea, the market for the product, and the target audience have been defined.

Hypotheses to substantiate the potential idea have been formulated.

The data that you will need to test the hypothesis you have put forward has been cleaned.

The hypotheses have been tested by calculating statistics, using pivot tables, filtering, and by grouping the cleaned data.
Complete the data research stage: check the remaining hypotheses, and select the material for visualization.

